        <h3 class="step-item__title">Meet your coach</h3>
        <p class="step-item__desc">Every lifter starts with an intake session — movement assessment, training history, current numbers, and your competition goals. No program starts without this.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step-item">
        <span class="step-item__number" aria-hidden="true">2</span>
        <h3 class="step-item__title">Structured programming</h3>
        <p class="step-item__desc">Evidence-based periodization built around your timeline and goals. Squat, bench, deadlift — programmed with purpose, not guesswork.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step-item">
        <span class="step-item__number" aria-hidden="true">3</span>
        <h3 class="step-item__title">Competition prep</h3>
        <p class="step-item__desc">Peak programming, attempt selection, weigh-in strategy, warm-up timing — your coach handles the full meet-day experience so you can focus on lifting.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step-item">
        <span class="step-item__number" aria-hidden="true">4</span>
        <h3 class="step-item__title">Community accountability</h3>
        <p class="step-item__desc">The Southwest Strength Club team trains and competes together. PRs get celebrated. Hard blocks get shared. You won't do this alone.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
